<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Political_corruption&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Corruption in fiction">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Corruption in fiction</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Financier" title="The Financier">The Financier</a></i> (1912), <i><a href="/wiki/The_Titan" title="The Titan">The Titan</a></i> (1914), and <i><a href="/wiki/The_Stoic" title="The Stoic">The Stoic</a></i> (1947), <a href="/wiki/Theodore_Dreiser" title="Theodore Dreiser">Theodore Dreiser</a>'s <i>Trilogy of Desire</i>, based on the life of the notorious transit mogul <a href="/wiki/Charles_Tyson_Yerkes" title="Charles Tyson Yerkes" class="mw-redirect">Charles Tyson Yerkes</a></li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/Mr._Smith_Goes_to_Washington" title="Mr. Smith Goes to Washington">Mr. Smith Goes to Washington</a></i> (<a href="/wiki/1939_in_film" title="1939 in film">1939</a>)</li>
